{"key":"post-7585314","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>7585314</id>\n<content>Get rid of the heater.  Normal room temperature works best for fruiting.  As you said, use perlite for humidification.  In addition, colonizing trays shouldn't be in a tub.  They should be covered with foil and sitting on a shelf.  If they've been in the bottom of a tub, there's a chance that the CO2 levels got too high, stunting growth.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>7586238</next>\n<prev>7585148</prev>\n<first>7585148</first>\n<last>7586238</last>\n<when>1193967176</when>\n<utime>11/02/07 04:32 AM</utime>\n</post>"}